{
  "texts": [
    "The study by Kim et al. (2021) focuses on addressing the challenges of Named Entity Recognition (NER) in contemporary written texts, particularly the need for updated, labeled corpora that reflect recent linguistic changes.",
    "Traditional NER models, which rely heavily on supervised learning and annotated datasets like CoNLL 2003, struggle to perform effectively on more recent data due to outdated content.",
    "This research proposes a method for adapting NER models using distant supervision, which generates weakly labeled data from large, unannotated corpora such as Wikipedia and news articles.",
    "The goal is to improve the accuracy of NER in real-world, contemporary texts without requiring extensive manual annotation.",
    "The authors employ a distant supervision approach to automatically label unlabeled text from contemporary sources."
  ]
}